d me on March 5th to ask me if I was interested to take over ownership of his project. Fast-forward to the present; I will release a new version of AsyncJS on March 13th on wordpress.org, which will:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>integrate all &#8220;pro&#8221; features (that&#8217;s right, free for all)</li>\n<li>include some rewritten code for easier maintenance</li>\n<li>be fully i18n-ready (lots of strings to translate :-) )</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I will provide support on <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/async-javascript\">the wordpress.org forum</a> (be patient though, I don&#8217;t have a deep understanding of code, functionality &amp; quirks yet). I also have some more fixes/ smaller changes/ micro-improvements in mind (well, a Trello-board really) for the next release, but I am not planning major changes or new functionality. But I vaguely remember <a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2013/01/07/adopting-an-oss-orphan-autoptimize/\">I said something similar about Autoptimize a long time ago</a> and look where that got me &#8230;</p>\n<p>Anyway, <strong>kudo&#8217;s to David</strong> for a great plugin with a substantial user-base (over 30K active installations) and for doing &#8220;the right thing&#8221; (as in not putting it on the plugin-market in search for the highest bidder). I hope I&#8217;ll do you proud man!</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2012/11/06/dipping-below-the-magical-1-second-page-load-time/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Dipping below the magical 1 second page load time\">Dipping below the magical 1 second page load time </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2013/04/01/easter-bunny-special-autoptimize-1-6-0/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Easter Bunny special: Autoptimize 1.6.0\">Easter Bunny special: Autoptimize 1.6.0 </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2016/03/15/why-would-you-still-be-on-php-5-2/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Why would you still be on PHP 5.2?\">Why would you still be on PHP 5.2? </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~4/LRQIu2AuDQI\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\" alt=\"\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/03/13/taking-over-async-javascript-wordpress-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"4\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/03/13/taking-over-async-javascript-wordpress-plugin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"Long overdue: WP YouTube Lyte update\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:63:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/futtta_wordpress/~3/CsU1_E4k5sg/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/03/07/long-overdue-wp-youtube-lyte-update/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"